Archer: If they're going to Totemtaff, they've got to take this road...
Swordsman: I heard the princess is gorgeous. I want to check her out~
Archer: I also heard that she is gentle and warm-hearted. If I could just be one of her bodyguards...
Naya: You'd definitely be happy about your job, right?
Archer: That's right!!
Archer: ......
Swordsman: Waaahhh!!! Lieutenant Rosset!
Naya: You two! How dare you abandon your posts and come here to goof around!?
Swordsman: W-W-W-We're sorry!
Archer: We h-h-heard the Princess was coming to visit the Bears, so we thought we could get a peek at her...
Naya: You leave your post and you're full of excuses. Get the hell back there!
Swordsman: Yes, ma'am...
Naya: (Now that he mentioned it, I haven't seen Angelia in a while, either...)
Naya: (I'm almost off work. I ought to go see her before she heads out...)
Flustered Soldier: Lieutenant Rosset, there you are! I've been looking everywhere for you!
Naya: What's wrong?
Flustered Soldier: I've just received news that monsters have appeared on the Prairie!
Naya: What!? Isn't the void's next exhale cycle expected to begin in 15 days?
Flustered Soldier: The officer is not sure, ma'am. But I'm afraid that several witnesses have already come forward...
Naya: (The void's cycles have been gradually destabilizing these past few years. Could there be something wrong with the Academy's predictions...?)
Flustered Soldier: Lieutenant Rosset?
Naya: Luckily for us, I just caught two buggers skipping work. No need to call for support. Lead the way!
Flustered Soldier: Yes, ma'am!
Flustered Soldier: The villager who made the report said this was the place...
Naya: Something looks off...
Swordsman: Lieutenant Rosset, if I'm not mistaken, this place is——
Pang: Watch out for that monster! Get behind me!
Tica: That's not a monster! Don't hurt him!
Flustered Soldier: Who's arguing? Are they talking about...
Naya: That way!
Swordsman: Wait, Lieutenant! I'm not finished talk——
Naya: Where are the monsters!?
Pang: Be careful! This girl is with the monsters!
Tica: I already told you, that's not a monster! Don't hurt him, otherwise I won't be able to face Professor Clovis~
Naya: Who the hell are you two?
Pang: Freeze!
Tica: Tica~  to the rescue!!!
Tica: Ouch! Sooo unfair...exploding right before you die...
Swordsman: Lieutenant Rosset!!
Archer: No, this way is blocked. There's no way through!
Naya: What's wrong with these Boomshrooms? They're usually so mild-tempered...
Swordsman: This is their nesting area! They're usually not this rough, but they need to protect the young ones...
Swordsman: I was born here, so I'm familiar with the area.
Naya: Why didn't you say something sooner!?
Swordsman: I was trying to tell you, but you weren't listening!
Naya: *tsk*...whatever. I'll do my best to take 'em out. You take care of yourselves!
Tica: Woooh! We made it out alive!
Pang: I never thought the 'shrooms would be so powerful...
Pang: Seeing is believing, my friend.
Naya: Don't even think about moving!
Naya: I'm Lieutenant Naya Rosset, a ranking Royal Security Officer. I've got a few questions I'd like to ask you.
